cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI 

The paper deals with the identification of switched autoregressive exogenous (SARX) linear models, which is a topic related to system identification and control theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves the computation of expected values and the use of large data sets, which are topics related to machine learning and statistics. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.ST (Statistics) are also likely categories. The paper uses input-output data to identify switched systems, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence and neural networks. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also possible categories. Finally, the paper deals with noisy data sets, which is a topic related to signal processing and information theory. Hence, cs.SI (Signal Processing) is also a possible category.
